      • ENERGY STAR CERTIFIED - Cielo Smart Thermostat guarantees you savings on your heating and cooling bills. Smart Choice for Savings - Huge saving on your heating and cooling costs.

Power: R Rc, Rh, C.

            How customer reviews and ratings work

            Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

            To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

            • TomC
              4.0 out of 5 stars Very capable and cost effective
              Reviewed in the United States on July 11, 2023
              Verified Purchase
              I bought this Cielo smart thermostat to control my central HVAC for two reasons. First, because the price was substantially better than the price of the Nest or Ecobee thermostats (the two most highly rated smart thermostats on Amazon), and because I already had two Cielo Breez thermostats for controlling my mini splits and I wanted to control everything from one App rather than multiple Apps. The mini split controlling units are absolutely terrific so I figured this might also be as good. Well this thermostat is very good but it’s not quite as perfect as the Breez ECO, Plus, and Max mini split controllers.

              What I like is that it is very easy to install with clear and simple instructions. The unit comes with a C-wire adapter, which I didn’t need but that seems a plus for installations where a C-wire isn’t available. When you’ve installed and connected the thermostat the screen on it tells you what it has detected and that confirms whether your connections are correct or need to be adjusted.

              It has loads of functionality but this is where things get less simple and easy. The unit comes with four available modes, Home, Away, Pets, and Sleep. I figured I would setup the Home mode with preset temperature changes during the day to account for breakfast hours, time away from home, evening relaxation, and sleep time. Well not so fast….. It turns out that Home doesn’t have multiple times available. Instead Home is one preset for which you set the time it activates and the days it is active but then you must create other presets with different names to manage alternative temperatures and times and days they will activate. This is all very complicated and makes it hard to configure different temperatures profiles for a weekend. Sleep seems to me to be a lessor included option within Home, but no, that’s another preset option.

              As another reviewer has observed, their support line is answered fast (during their business hours of 9am-9pm M-F), is staffed with extremely knowledgeable and helpful agents, and they are very willing and able to walk you through the setup process. In my view it just shouldn’t be as hard as they have made it. Setup should be more intuitive, not require tech support, and it should be designed to meet the needs of the actual user not the designer.

              In summary, the functioning of this new offering from Cielo is excellent and with some improvements to the programming process and their remote control App it will be one of the best on the market. In the meantime if does everything the others do but it takes a bit more effort than it should.
